<item>
            <title>[JDK-8258776] ThreadLocal#initialValue() Javadoc is unaware of ThreadLocal#withInitial()</title>
                <link>https://bugs.openjdk.org/browse/JDK-8258776</link>
                <project id="10100" key="JDK">JDK</project>
                    <description>A DESCRIPTION OF THE PROBLEM :&lt;br/&gt;
Javadoc of ThreadLocal#initialValue() states:&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;if the programmer desires thread-local variables to have an initial value other than null, ThreadLocal must be subclassed&lt;br/&gt;
This has been there before Java 8 and now seems to suggest a non-recommended way as there is ThreadLocal#withInitial() now which serves the same purpose but is simpler and does not require subclassing.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
Thus the Javadoc should be changed to recommend the latter approach.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
</description>
